- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the article focuses on comparing performance penalties of different virtualization methods for HPC applications, which is a common topic in distributed and parallel computing.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the article discusses the influence of networking connection type on application performance.
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is relevant as the article compares the performance of different virtualization methods, which is related to the operating system.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the article discusses the use of Docker containers for creating isolated environments for HPC applications, which is a common topic in software engineering.
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the article focuses on comparing the performance of different virtualization methods for HPC applications.
